entries.title: Search continues for mother of 3 missing since Jan. 1
entries.description: The search continues for 39-year-old Ana Walshe, a Massachusetts mother of three who was last seen on New Year's Day leaving for a flight she never took, police said.

entries.title: Musk says he can't get fair trial in California, wants Texas
entries.description: Elon Musk doesn't think he can get a fair trial in San Francisco.

entries.title: New Mexico delegation seeks changes to wildfire aid rules
entries.description: FEMA is preparing to wrap up public comment on the rules.

entries.title: Thousands of Israelis protest new government's policies
entries.description: Opponents say Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s policies threaten democracy.

entries.title: Subway train collision in Mexico City kills 1, injures 41
entries.description: Authorities in Mexico City say two subway trains have collided between stations, killing at least one person and injuring 41

entries.title: 1 killed, 2 wounded in shooting near Hollywood Walk of Fame
entries.description: Police say a man was killed and two others were wounded in a shooting early Saturday near the Hollywood Walk of Fame

entries.title: Doctor accused of sex assault by former presidential candidate's wife trial to begin
entries.description: Columbia University OBGYN Dr. Robert Hadden sex assault trial to start Monday.

entries.title: Prosecutors launch website to notify Sam Bankman-Fried's alleged victims
entries.description: Prosecutors launched a website to notify Sam Bankman-Fried's alleged victims of his FTX company.

entries.title: Woman gets 3 years in bogus good Samaritan online fundraiser
entries.description: A New Jersey woman who pleaded guilty to helping her boyfriend spread a feel-good story that garnered more than $400,000 in online donations has been sentenced to three years in prison on state theft charges

entries.title: W.Va. journalist let go after reporting on abuse allegations
entries.description: A West Virginia journalist lost her job after she reported about alleged abuse of people with disabilities in state care

entries.title: Trial set for Black soldier suing police over violent stop
entries.description: A U.S. Army lieutenant who was pepper sprayed, struck and handcuffed by police in Virginia but never arrested will argue to a jury next week that he was assaulted and falsely imprisoned and that his vehicle was illegally searched

entries.title: Intoxicated man desecrates altar with sledgehammer, steals 1,500 year-old relics
entries.description: Intoxicated man desecrates altar with sledgehammer, steals 1,500 year-old relics.

entries.title: China suspends social media accounts of COVID policy critics
entries.description: China has suspended or closed the social media accounts of more than 1,000 critics of the government's policies on the COVID-19 outbreak, as the country moves to roll back harsh anti-virus restrictions

entries.title: UK leader calls crisis meeting over struggling health system
entries.description: British Prime Minister Rishi Sunak is gathering government ministers, medics and health service managers in 10 Downing St. for talks aimed at fixing a health care crisis that has seen thousands of patients stranded outside overflowing hospitals

entries.title: Sinking land forces hundreds to leave Indian temple town
entries.description: Authorities in an Indian Himalayan town have stopped construction activities and started moving hundreds of people to temporary shelters after a temple collapsed and cracks appeared in over 600 houses because of sinking of land

entries.title: Iran executes 2 more men detained amid nationwide protests
entries.description: Iran says it has executed two men convicted of allegedly killing a paramilitary volunteer, the latest executions aimed at halting the nationwide protests now challenging the country’s theocracy

entries.title: Organ transporter braves snowstorm to get kidney to recipient on Christmas Eve
entries.description: A Minnesota organ transporter and sheriff braced through heavy snow and high winds in two states to help a patient.

entries.title: Venus Williams out of Australian Open due to injury
entries.description: Venus Williams has withdrawn from the Australian Open for an undisclosed injury she sustained while playing in a tournament in Auckland, New Zealand this week

entries.title: Utah murder-suicide underscores frequency of family killings
entries.description: A murder-suicide that left eight members of one family including five children dead in a small Utah town is the latest in what has become an all-too-common occurrence in troubled households across the United States

entries.title: Winning numbers drawn for Mega Millions jackpot nearing $1 billion
entries.description: The winning numbers were drawn Friday night for the Mega Millions jackpot worth an estimated $940 million.

entries.title: Family of slain Utah family says husband took guns from home
entries.description: A Utah man who fatally shot his five children, mother-in-law and wife and then killed himself had removed guns owned by himself and his wife days before the murder-suicide, leaving the family “vulnerable,” a relative said Friday

entries.title: Suspect in NYPD machete attack indicted by grand jury on attempted murder charges
entries.description: The 19-year-old suspect arrested in connection with the blade attack against New York City cops was indicted on several charges.

entries.title: Judge scolds Trump lawyers, denies bid to toss fraud lawsuit
entries.description: A Manhattan judge on Friday scolded Donald Trump’s lawyers as he denied their bid to dismiss a lawsuit accusing the former president and his company of a yearslong fraud scheme

entries.title: Wall Street Journal reporter handcuffed by Phoenix police officer
entries.description: The Phoenix PD is launching an investigation after an officer handcuffed and detained a WSJ reporter in November.
